info.title: Captain Data API v2
info.description:
Welcome to Captain Data API (v2) allowing you to used and view workflows, jobs and integrations.

If you're having any trouble using this API, shoot us an email at [support@captaindata.co](support@captaindata.co).

If you're looking for the Documentation v1 (deprecated), checkout [https://docs.v1.captaindata.co](https://docs.v1.captaindata.co)

get.description: Returns basic information about your project, such as the number of tasks used and left.
This endpoint lists all the workflows you created.

example.error: The project uid you provided is not UUID.

post.description:
You may schedule a specific workflow using this endpoint. You can inject inputs: ```json "inputs": [ "url.com", "url2.com" ] ```

You can specify metadata to be sent with the inputs, as such: ```json "inputs": [ { "url": "url.com", "meta": {"id": "some_ID", "key": "other_key"} }, { "url": "url2.com", "meta": {"id": "some_ID2", "key": "other_key2"} }, ] ```

Specify any input parameters specific to the workflow's configuration: ```json "input_parameters": { "key": "value" } ```

You can use specific integration accounts you previously synchronized: ```json "integrations": { "xxxx-xxxx-xxxx": {} } ```
With `xxxx-xxxx-xxxx` being the account_uid you want to use.

Finally, you can specify a delay in order to schedule the job later. ```json "delay": 3600 ```
With 3600 which is the difference, in seconds, between now and the time at which you want to schedule the job.

You can read more about this subject on our Help Center.

example.job_name: If you want to pass a specific job name
example.templated_uid: If you need to schedule a specific step in a workflow (only use if you know what you're doing)

example.error: inputs must be a list OR You must supply a list of inputs (even empty).

post.description:
You may retry a specific job using this endpoint. Specify any input parameters specific to the workflow's configuration: ```json "input_parameters": { "key": "value" } ```

You can use specific integration accounts you previously synchronized: ```json "integrations": { "xxxx-xxxx-xxxx": {} } ```
With `xxxx-xxxx-xxxx` being the account_uid you want to use.

Finally, you can specify a delay in order to retry the job later. ```json "delay": 3600 ```
With 3600 which is the difference, in seconds, between now and the time at which you want to retry the job.

You can read more about this subject on our Help Center.

example.job_name: If you want to pass a specific job name
example.delay: If you want to retry job in a while.

post.description:
This endpoint stops a specific Job UID.

All running inputs that have not been run will be marked as `stopped`.

The job itself will be marked as `stopped`.

get.description:
This endpoint enables you to retrieve inputs for a specific job UID.

Inputs can have multiple status values:
- `pending`: the input is going to run asap
- `invalid`: the input payload is not valid (not respecting certain rules)
- `valid`: the input payload respects the task's rules
- `running`: the input is actually running
- `success`: the input has finished successfully
- `failed`: the input has failed
- `queued`: the input is scheduled to be run in the future
- `stopped`: the input has been stopped by you (via API or manually)

parameters.name: job_uid
parameters.description: The Job UID to fetch inputs from.

get.description:
This endpoint returns all the account details 
- the value used for the accounts
- its level (e.g. for LinkedIn `Classic` or `Sales Navigator`)
- limits consumption

**Limits Consumption**
For almost each integrations, we're setting specific limitations.

Such limitations can be updated.

Here's the detail for the keys:
- `item_scraped`: the number of items extracted for the template
- `level`: the account's level
- `limit_name`: e.g. `profile enrichments`
- `limit_value`: the current limit value
- `permalink`: the unique limit name to be used inside your code
- `start_time_range`: 
- `end_time_range`: 
- `templates`: the list (`array`) of templates UID that you're using that are linked with the limit

parameters.description: The integration path to fetch the account from.

parameters.description: The account you want to fetch.

tags.name: Collections
tags.description:
Collections are a brand new way to create and interact with databases.

> Make sure to use the proper domain endpoint, which is different than the classic `api.captaindata.co` domain.

## People Collections
At the moment, only the workflow `LinkedIn Sequence` is compatible with this system.

The collection is named `people`.

#### People Collections Schemas
List of available `schema` type for the `People` collection:
- `sequence` used to query sequence leads that have been imported in the sequence
- `connection` used to save an account's connections
